From fb8453ce6eace5308defb8c75ce99d34febea7d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 16:24:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Big-endian and PowerPC architecture support

Core changes:
- config.h: Add PowerPC (32-bit and 64-bit) CPU detection with proper
            endianness detection using __BYTE_ORDER__. Remove #error
            directive that blocked big-endian builds.
- Ops.h: Remove #error blocking big-endian builds. Add #ifdef CPU_LE
         conditional for Peek/Poke le/be functions to swap correctly
         on both little-endian and big-endian systems.
- Defs.h: Add CPU_LE conditionals for MAKEWORD/MAKELONG/MAKEQWORD
          macros to maintain chr[] array index compatibility on BE.
- Value.h: Replace type-punning pointer access with memcpy-based
           SetPtr/GetPtr/SetRefType/GetRefType for endianness safety.
- Value.cpp: Update ptr() assignments to use SetPtr() method.

Draw fixes:
- Drawing.cpp: Fix StreamPackPoints writing part_count*4 instead of *8
               (upstream bug affecting non-8-byte Point systems).
               Remove unnecessary (short) casts in StreamUnpackPoints.
               Add big-endian wchar handling in DrawTextOp and reader.

Plugin fixes:
- plugin/bmp/bmphdr.h: Replace non-existent UPP::SwapEndian() with
                       Upp::EndianSwap().
- plugin/bmp/_bmp.h: Fix recursive EndianSwap() calls to use
                     Upp::EndianSwap(). Remove outdated #error.
- plugin/pcx/pcxhdr.h: Fix SwapEndian() to use correct PCX field names
                       instead of copy-pasted BMP field names.

These fixes enable building on PowerPC and other big-endian architectures.
